HEADWORD: Alluvium
<hw>Al*lu"vi*um</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Alluviums</plw>, L. <plw>Alluvia</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L., neut. of <ets>alluvius</ets>. See <er>Alluvious</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Deposits of earth, sand, gravel, and other
transported matter, made by rivers, floods, or other causes, upon land
not permanently submerged beneath the waters of lakes or seas.</def>
<rj><au>Lyell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

